M|saas-economics-efficiency-metrics|- [ ] Gross margin >70% (SaaS should be high-margin)
M|saas-economics-efficiency-metrics|- [ ] LTV:CAC >3:1 (minimum for sustainable growth)
M|saas-economics-efficiency-metrics|- [ ] Payback period <12 months (cash efficient)
M|saas-economics-efficiency-metrics|- [ ] Contribution margin >60% (after all variable costs)
M|saas-economics-efficiency-metrics|- [ ] LTV calculated with gross margin (not just revenue)
M|saas-economics-efficiency-metrics|- [ ] Runway >12 months (healthy buffer)
M|saas-economics-efficiency-metrics|- [ ] Net burn decreasing over time (path to profitability)
M|saas-economics-efficiency-metrics|- [ ] OpEx growing slower than revenue (positive operating leverage)
M|saas-economics-efficiency-metrics|- [ ] G&A <15% of revenue (keep overhead low)
M|saas-economics-efficiency-metrics|- [ ] Rule of 40 >40 (healthy balance)
M|saas-economics-efficiency-metrics|- [ ] Magic number >0.75 (efficient GTM)
M|saas-economics-efficiency-metrics|- [ ] Revenue growth rate > OpEx growth rate (operating leverage)
M|saas-economics-efficiency-metrics|Check if any of these apply:
M|saas-economics-efficiency-metrics|- [ ] LTV:CAC <1.5:1 (buying revenue at a loss)
M|saas-economics-efficiency-metrics|- [ ] Payback period >24 months (cash trap)
M|saas-economics-efficiency-metrics|- [ ] Runway <6 months (survival crisis)
M|saas-economics-efficiency-metrics|- [ ] Rule of 40 <25 (burning cash without growth)
M|saas-economics-efficiency-metrics|- [ ] Magic number <0.5 (GTM engine broken)
M|saas-economics-efficiency-metrics|- [ ] OpEx growing faster than revenue (negative leverage)
M|saas-economics-efficiency-metrics|- [ ] Gross margin <60% (margin problem)
M|saas-economics-efficiency-metrics|- [ ] CAC increasing while LTV flat/decreasing (unit economics degrading)
M|saas-economics-efficiency-metrics|- [ ] Great LTV:CAC but terrible payback (illusion of health)
M|saas-economics-efficiency-metrics|**If you checked any red flags, see SKILL.md Common Pitfalls section for fixes.**